headline: Aon: Q1 Earnings Snapshot
summary: DUBLIN (AP) — Aon PLC (AON) on Friday reported first-quarter profit of $965 million. On a per-share basis, the Dublin-based company said it had net income of $4.43. Earnings, adjusted for non-recurring costs, were $5.67 per share.
